div.p:
We are still mourning A Gray's death;
Asa Gray died on 30 January 1888. he & Mrs Gray spent last summer in Europe, & made a tour with us in Normandy, & he left this house for his home at the end of September in perfect health. I had known him intimately since 1858. You will find a notice of him by now in "Nature"
Hooker (1888). —
